<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 5:29PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Carter
County through 630 PM MDT...
At 529 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Alzada, or 35 miles northwest of Belle Fourche,
moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albion.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
